<table width=90% cellspacing=8 border=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td><font size=3>This guide explains how to  integrate XCache into PHP5 on a Debian Etch system (with Apache2). From the XCache project page: "XCache is a fast, stable PHP opcode cacher that has been tested and is now running on production servers under high load." It's similar to other PHP opcode cachers, such as eAccelerator and APC. <a href="http://www.howtoforge.com/xcache-php5-apache2-debian-etch">read more...</a></font></table></table><tr><td><font size=2 color=#666666><a href="?inode=11876">permapage</a> | score:9896 | </font><font size=2> -falko, April 3, 2008</table><table><tr><td height=8></table>
